rComments: One of the highest grades I have recieved during my 3 years here. The material is straightforward and so are the term tests if you can memorize the overarching ideas for each vitamin/mineral taught.

Somehow everyone managed to do poorly despite the fact that we all came to class and *tried* to pay attention. She gets off-topic a lot and talks about herself, rather than focusing on the lecture material. The midterms were bogus (we had to write 3 last year) and the class average was low. Don't take this course.

Seems to care. but leaves the marking to the TA's. random marks docked off randomly with a checkmark attached with no further comments. you can know your material, but the marking is arbitrary with the class average being 60%   don't take NFS382
